  {
    "client_msg_id": "D14880D7-F6B5-4222-81AF-D69182B2C4B9",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Watched through it and I think the direction you have taken is pretty solid. Though there are no fancy demos this time around, can see this as taking some neat moves that will pay off in the (immediate) future. Also carving out the problem space to just map projections for now is a smart move. Will help you focus on solving bug problems one step at a time. All in all, pretty promising and would love to see what comes out.\n\nOne question I had was: How would you declare constants and static snapshot of a dynamic thing in this environment? Like a constant is a variable that doesnt change, so thats easy to pull off but with re: static, I mean something that was dynamic and bound previously, but now you need to reify the result as a sort of new input to another function but not with the bindings. Is there a way to bind and unbind variables like this? I could supply an example if that description was not clear.",
