  {
    "client_msg_id": "8F5409BF-0933-4BDC-AEF7-E5BCB9EA3B11",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Reify was probably the wrong word choice here, but what I meant was, say you have an intermediate value in the middle of a function execution. You want to extract out this value and make it a static thing instead of it acting in the continuum. How would you accomplish that? Like say you have x = 10 points with x, y coordinates. Then you perform, reflectHorizontally(rotate(x)) generating a set of points. My impression with the two demos is that the value x is bound continuously throughout the transformation in the env. Now, you want to extract out, elements 1,2, and 7 out of the result and then store it as y which you will pipe through another set of transformations to produce z. So rewinding the story so far, we have x morphing into y morphing into z. Now, in a typical bound set up, the changes in x will be continuously mirrored to y and z. What I meant by static is, y when reified/extracted out of this abstract chain, will become a sort of end product of the transformation of x and  then become a non-live value changing/parametrizing which will change z independent of transformations that can happen to x. Hope the use case I had in mind is conveyed with this.",
